03:01.767 --> 03:02.700
Cal: hey.

03:02.767 --> 03:03.700
Hey. whoo.

03:03.767 --> 03:05.034
Where are we going?

03:05.101 --> 03:06.800
Surprise. oh.
divorce present.

03:06.867 --> 03:09.934
Wasn't planning to toast
the demise of my marriage,

03:10.000 --> 03:11.301
But thanks.

03:11.367 --> 03:12.367
How you feeling?

03:12.434 --> 03:13.367
Horrible,

03:13.434 --> 03:15.267
Depressed,
like a loser.

03:16.034 --> 03:17.568
You're happy.

03:17.633 --> 03:19.767
I'm not happy.
i'm devastated.

03:24.501 --> 03:26.234
All right,
trisha howell,

03:26.301 --> 03:27.967
She's a georgetown
law student,

03:28.034 --> 03:32.501
And she claims
she had a psychic vision
of a murder.

03:32.568 --> 03:34.534
I understand
the scientist in you

03:34.600 --> 03:37.234
Sees every day
as an opportunity
to discover

03:37.301 --> 03:39.134
Something new and wonderful
about the brain,

03:39.201 --> 03:41.367
But come on.
you don't believe in psychics.

03:41.434 --> 03:43.700
Well, as of now,
i'm switzerland.

03:43.767 --> 03:45.733
Plus our plate
is too full for this.

03:45.800 --> 03:47.733
We have a potential
supreme court nominee to vet.

03:47.800 --> 03:49.800
Well, i do believe
there's a scientific

03:49.867 --> 03:52.534
Explanation
for what she saw.

03:55.501 --> 03:58.934
Uh, trisha howell,
this is, uh,
gillian foster.

03:59.000 --> 04:03.633
Why don't you
tell foster here
about your vision.

04:03.700 --> 04:05.900
Um, i started
writing it down,

04:05.967 --> 04:08.468
But, um, i saw a man...

04:08.534 --> 04:11.800
Tall, short black hair,
blue eyes.

04:11.867 --> 04:16.966
He's in a hotel, room 202,
and he's freaking out.

04:17.034 --> 04:19.867
There's blood all over.

04:19.934 --> 04:22.767
Whose blood was it?
did you see a victim?

04:22.834 --> 04:25.700
Just an ashtray
smashing down,

04:25.767 --> 04:27.267
And then he's running, and...

04:27.334 --> 04:29.900
The hotel sign has
some kind of a devil on it.

04:29.967 --> 04:31.568
It's, uh--

04:31.633 --> 04:35.367
It's by that druggie park
over off of "l" street.

04:35.434 --> 04:38.733
Can you excuse us
for just one moment?

04:45.600 --> 04:48.468
That was a smooth exit line.
it was very professional.

04:48.534 --> 04:51.733
This is a matter
for the police or
a magic 8-ball.

04:51.800 --> 04:53.067
Right, these are
the options--

04:53.134 --> 04:55.667
One...

04:55.733 --> 04:57.234
Trisha's ill;

04:57.301 --> 04:59.468
2, she actually
is a psychic;

04:59.534 --> 05:01.800
3, she witnessed
a murder

05:01.867 --> 05:04.034
And no one
believes her.

05:04.101 --> 05:06.667
In any of these cases,
she needs our help,
right?

05:07.800 --> 05:09.334
Agent reynolds is waiting
with judge simon.

05:09.401 --> 05:11.301
Potential
supreme court nominee.

05:11.367 --> 05:13.067
Mmm.

05:13.134 --> 05:14.733
Right.

05:15.834 --> 05:17.067
Ah, here he is.

05:17.134 --> 05:19.401
Judge simon, this is
dr. cal lightman.

05:19.468 --> 05:22.167
Glad you could
clear your schedule
on such short notice.

05:22.234 --> 05:24.501
Yeah, well,
i couldn't, actually.
this is ria torres.

05:24.568 --> 05:28.267
She's gonna determine
whether or not you're
a lying son of a bitch.

05:29.733 --> 05:32.034
[gasps] just one...

05:35.000 --> 05:36.468
The president
specifically
asked for you.

05:36.534 --> 05:39.401
You do know i can tell
when you're lying, don't you?

05:39.468 --> 05:40.667
Yeah, well,
how 'bout this?

05:40.733 --> 05:42.568
Vetting this guy
is the f.b.i.'s
responsibility,

05:42.633 --> 05:44.600
And you have
a contractual obligation

05:44.667 --> 05:45.967
To give f.b.i. cases
top priority.

05:46.034 --> 05:47.934
Lightman group
has that obligation,
not lightman proper.

05:48.000 --> 05:50.234
And, uh, torres
is a natural, remember?
she's gonna do fine.

05:50.301 --> 05:51.700
No, fine's not gonna cut it.

05:51.767 --> 05:53.700
If this guy's got
some deep, dark secrets--

05:53.767 --> 05:55.434
He does. he does.
we all do.

05:55.501 --> 05:56.468
Let me be clear.

05:56.534 --> 05:58.434
My ass is on the line.

05:58.501 --> 05:59.967
Zoe.

06:00.867 --> 06:02.667
I was just
gonna call you.

06:02.733 --> 06:04.900
I saved you the trouble.
hi, ben.

06:04.967 --> 06:05.900
Hey.
testy ex-wife

06:05.967 --> 06:07.834
Trumps testy
f.b.i. agent.
excuse us.

06:07.900 --> 06:08.900
We're not done.

06:08.967 --> 06:10.700
Always nice
to see you, zoe.

06:10.767 --> 06:12.067
Nice to see you, ben.

06:12.134 --> 06:16.434
Emily says you've
been good weird.
she's concerned.

06:16.501 --> 06:18.234
I quit the department
of justice.

06:18.301 --> 06:21.568
I'm moving to chicago
to head up my own practice.

06:22.600 --> 06:24.834
What does emily have
to say about this?

06:24.900 --> 06:27.134
She doesn't know yet,
and since she'll wonder

06:27.201 --> 06:29.134
Why i'm not
going in to work,

06:29.201 --> 06:32.501
I figured we should
probably tell her
before then, say, today.

06:33.767 --> 06:35.967
Well, chicago's
a nice town.

06:36.034 --> 06:37.301
Not close, though.

06:37.367 --> 06:39.834
Well, you were always
the one who said
if i had any guts,

06:39.900 --> 06:41.401
I would start
my own law firm.

06:41.468 --> 06:42.401
Yeah, but, chicago?

06:42.468 --> 06:44.067
You remember dave gruber
from law school?

06:44.134 --> 06:45.568
The handsy, flirty guy.

06:45.633 --> 06:47.000
Heh.

06:47.067 --> 06:49.600
You're gonna work for
the handsy, flirty guy?

06:49.667 --> 06:51.334
No, i'm not going to be
working for him.

06:51.401 --> 06:53.501
I'm gonna be
running a new branch
of his law firm.

06:53.568 --> 06:54.800
Yeah, but still
not your firm, though.

06:54.867 --> 06:56.733
I knew you would
try to make me
change my mind,

06:56.800 --> 06:59.568
And i'm not
going to, ok? it's done,
so just be happy for me.

06:59.633 --> 07:01.600
I am happy for you.
good.

07:01.667 --> 07:04.900
It'd just be
quite an adjustment for emily.

07:04.967 --> 07:07.700
It'll take time.

07:07.767 --> 07:09.468
She's an amazing kid.

07:11.800 --> 07:14.434
You wanna take emily
to chicago.

07:14.501 --> 07:15.900
I've already
made a schedule

07:15.967 --> 07:17.934
Where you can have her
for the holidays,

07:18.000 --> 07:21.367
And, you know, you're
free to come to chicago
any time you want.

07:21.434 --> 07:23.034
You know,
we can make this work.

07:23.101 --> 07:25.234
Look, i'm not saying
it's not selfish,

07:25.301 --> 07:27.000
But the right thing
for me

07:27.067 --> 07:29.900
Also happens
to be the right thing
for emily.

07:32.167 --> 07:34.000
Don't do that.

07:34.067 --> 07:37.667
You know i hate it
when you do that.

07:48.101 --> 07:49.700
Thanks for waiting,
judge simon.

07:49.767 --> 07:54.733
I came here
fully prepared to be
vetted by an expert.

07:54.800 --> 07:56.867
How old are you?

07:56.934 --> 07:58.733
24.

08:04.900 --> 08:06.234
Let's get started.

08:13.667 --> 08:14.700
Where's the girl?

08:14.767 --> 08:16.800
There was a girl
in there claiming

08:16.867 --> 08:18.534
Psychic abilities.
where is she?

08:21.334 --> 08:22.568
Where's the girl?

08:22.633 --> 08:26.067
Oh. do we have
funds for a study
on herd behavior?

08:26.134 --> 08:27.334
The girl,
where is she?

08:27.401 --> 08:29.101
She left.
oh, and you let her?

08:29.167 --> 08:31.134
I run a research lab,
not a prison.

08:31.201 --> 08:32.433
She wanted to leave.
she left.

08:32.501 --> 08:34.167
Where are you going?

08:34.234 --> 08:35.568
None of my business.

08:35.633 --> 08:38.433
Check. power of nonverbal
communication. awesome. love it.

08:38.501 --> 08:41.366
Boom.

08:52.468 --> 08:54.633
You got a room?

08:54.700 --> 08:56.468
You lookin' for company?

08:56.534 --> 08:57.468
Uh, no.

08:57.534 --> 08:58.733
Not in this economy.

08:58.800 --> 09:01.501
I'll settle for
the porn package.

09:21.667 --> 09:23.867
Well, that does
appear to be blood.

09:23.934 --> 09:25.900
Well, we need
to find the girl.

09:25.967 --> 09:27.800
I assume you wanna
bring her downtown.

09:27.867 --> 09:29.367
The girl with
the psychic visions?

09:29.434 --> 09:30.967
Well, why don't
we just have her

09:31.034 --> 09:32.234
Give us tomorrow's
lottery numbers,

09:32.301 --> 09:34.000
And we can all
retire early?

09:34.867 --> 09:37.000
Nice to meet you.

09:38.334 --> 09:40.600
So this is what you
dragged me down here for.

09:40.667 --> 09:43.167
You know, every hotel room
this side of town

09:43.234 --> 09:46.267
Is gonna be ripe with blood
and various other
human discharges.

09:46.334 --> 09:47.834
No body, no crime.

09:48.733 --> 09:50.900
I'm gettin' back
to the judge.

09:50.967 --> 09:53.534
I suggest you do the same.

09:55.034 --> 09:58.301
Well, that's it for your,
you know, most prominent cases.

09:58.367 --> 10:04.367
Uh, let's move on
to your family.

10:04.434 --> 10:06.267
Ah. ok.

10:06.334 --> 10:09.101
Celia, your wife,
tell me about her.

10:09.167 --> 10:10.733
What would
you like to know?

10:10.800 --> 10:14.767
Uh, well, i guess the--
the big one is, uh,
have you ever cheated on her?

10:14.834 --> 10:17.900
I can't imagine
any senator on
the judiciary committee

10:17.967 --> 10:19.000
Asking me that.

10:19.067 --> 10:22.167
Oh, no. that's not--
i mean, i--i just--

10:22.234 --> 10:23.767
I have to ask you.

10:23.834 --> 10:25.101
The answer's no.

10:26.034 --> 10:27.468
So you've never
been interested

10:27.534 --> 10:29.334
In another woman
in that time?

10:29.401 --> 10:30.900
Never.

10:32.367 --> 10:35.267
Really?

10:35.334 --> 10:36.633
You never cheated?

10:36.700 --> 10:38.267
He said no.

10:39.201 --> 10:41.468
Did you ever cheat
on your taxes?

10:41.534 --> 10:43.167
Torres.

10:43.234 --> 10:44.101
No,

10:44.167 --> 10:45.568
And i've been
paying them

10:45.633 --> 10:47.401
Longer than you've
been breathing air.

10:47.468 --> 10:49.867
My age really bothers you.

10:49.934 --> 10:53.067
In my experience,
anybody under
the age of 35

10:53.134 --> 10:56.767
Normally doesn't
know their ass from
a hole in the ground.

10:56.834 --> 10:59.900
So, yes, the fact
that you're standing

10:59.967 --> 11:01.934
Between me
and a position

11:02.000 --> 11:05.201
On the supreme court
of the united states
of america

11:05.267 --> 11:07.067
Does not thrill me.

11:36.633 --> 11:38.501
Trisha.

11:42.534 --> 11:44.667
Found this
under the bed.

11:47.101 --> 11:48.867
Who are you?

11:48.934 --> 11:50.134
What do you want?

11:50.201 --> 11:52.201
Don't you know me?

11:52.267 --> 11:54.167
Oh, yeah, yeah.
i know you.

11:54.234 --> 11:56.568
You and me,
we're old friends, babe.

11:58.367 --> 11:59.767
Tell me your name.

11:59.834 --> 12:01.600
Why should i?

12:08.867 --> 12:10.134
It's jessie.

12:10.934 --> 12:12.267
I'm cal lightman.

12:12.334 --> 12:14.501
We met earlier today.

12:14.568 --> 12:16.934
Only, then you
were someone else.

12:17.000 --> 12:19.134
I'll be anybody
you want me to be.

12:19.201 --> 12:21.633
I wanna spend
some time with you.

12:22.867 --> 12:23.800
No.

12:23.867 --> 12:26.167
Not like that.

12:27.468 --> 12:29.834
I want you to meet
some friends of mine.

12:30.867 --> 12:32.834
Gonna cost you extra.

12:39.467 --> 12:41.800
Foster: the camera,
the strange white room.

12:41.867 --> 12:43.100
She's afraid.

12:44.067 --> 12:46.601
And we're about
to get funky.

12:47.668 --> 12:49.534
4 hours ago...

12:51.434 --> 12:54.833
Right before
she ran out of here.

12:54.900 --> 12:57.067
Shoulders back.
chest out.

12:57.134 --> 12:58.734
Totally different posture.

12:58.800 --> 13:01.134
Totally different girl.

13:01.200 --> 13:02.634
Eli: hello, hair.

13:02.701 --> 13:05.634
Trisha walked
into that room,
and jessie walked out.

13:05.701 --> 13:08.301
Yeah. for funsies,
i had...

13:08.367 --> 13:10.234
Hooker jessie
write down her
coffee order,

13:10.301 --> 13:13.601
And i compared
that to law student
trisha's account

13:13.668 --> 13:15.467
Of her
so-called vision.

13:15.534 --> 13:16.668
Night and day.

13:16.734 --> 13:17.734
These 2 documents

13:17.800 --> 13:19.467
Indicate
2 fundamentally

13:19.534 --> 13:21.701
Different
personalities.

13:21.768 --> 13:23.067
Trisha's got it,

13:23.134 --> 13:25.800
Multiple personality
disorder.

13:25.867 --> 13:27.367
The holy grail
of psychiatry.

13:27.434 --> 13:30.167
This is your
divorce present.

13:30.234 --> 13:31.967
It's dissociative
identity disorder,

13:32.034 --> 13:35.167
And it's--
it's more plausible than
a psychic phenomenon,

13:35.234 --> 13:36.167
But just barely.

13:36.234 --> 13:37.701
Of course,
if it is d.i.d.,

13:37.768 --> 13:39.167
There's empirical
evidence of explicit

13:39.234 --> 13:40.668
Memory transfer
in such cases.

13:40.734 --> 13:44.000
I mean, she could have--
she could have perceived
that as a vision.

13:44.067 --> 13:45.567
So her alter
witnessed a murder.

13:45.634 --> 13:48.200
Or committed a murder.

13:48.267 --> 13:51.567
No. no, this girl
didn't hurt anyone.

13:51.634 --> 13:52.900
If she had, her
other personalities

13:52.967 --> 13:54.933
Would never
have let her come
to me, right?

13:55.000 --> 13:58.301
Jessie probably
isn't the only alter.

13:58.367 --> 13:59.800
Right.

14:09.833 --> 14:13.034
You know i can see you
all out there staring at me.

14:13.100 --> 14:15.134
Loker.

14:21.900 --> 14:23.367
What the hell?

14:23.434 --> 14:25.434
Just giving you
some privacy.

14:25.501 --> 14:27.267
Met some freaks
in my time,

14:27.334 --> 14:29.100
But this place
is perv central.

14:29.167 --> 14:31.134
Oh, you might
have a point there.

14:31.200 --> 14:33.501
Guess if you're
payin' for it.

14:37.067 --> 14:40.134
Why'd you sneak
into that hotel room?

14:40.200 --> 14:41.634
Why did you?

14:41.701 --> 14:43.567
Were you trying
to cover up a crime?

14:43.634 --> 14:45.367
No.

14:45.434 --> 14:47.067
Lip curl,
forced eye contact.

14:47.134 --> 14:48.467
You're lying.

14:48.534 --> 14:50.833
I'm not some lab rat.

14:50.900 --> 14:52.833
Did you
kill somebody?

14:54.234 --> 14:56.167
No.

14:56.234 --> 14:57.833
Heart rate
and blood pressure
are steady.

14:57.900 --> 15:00.100
It's not determinate,
but she's believable.

15:00.167 --> 15:03.334
I'm gonna go see how jessie
feels about hypnosis.

15:03.401 --> 15:04.933
Bring your wallet.

15:06.567 --> 15:09.501
You presided over 16 cases
before your 35th birthday,

15:09.567 --> 15:11.833
<i>starting with
cahill v. wilson,</i>

15:11.900 --> 15:15.134
<i>then abandandou v. temple...</i>

15:16.567 --> 15:19.067
<i>ohio v. george.</i>

15:20.900 --> 15:24.234
<i>all right, ohio v. george.</i>

15:25.367 --> 15:27.401
Why do you have that reaction
to that case?

15:27.467 --> 15:29.167
What reaction?

15:29.234 --> 15:33.000
A drifter named bryce george
raped 56-year-old margaret lane.

15:33.067 --> 15:34.301
Where's agent reynolds?

15:34.367 --> 15:38.000
Busy. you gave him life
in prison for a first offense?

15:40.567 --> 15:44.501
You think i should
have given him
a lesser sentence?

15:46.434 --> 15:50.100
Agent reynolds doesn't
know that we've started
up again, does he?

15:50.167 --> 15:53.234
Did you have
a personal relationship
with margaret lane?

15:53.301 --> 15:55.634
No.

15:56.900 --> 16:00.401
I may be 24, but i have
a talent for spotting lies.

16:04.267 --> 16:05.467
Move on, ms. torres.

16:05.534 --> 16:07.867
You know, you really
shouldn't speak that way

16:07.933 --> 16:10.967
To the person
standing between you
and the supreme court.

16:15.701 --> 16:18.634
Just listen to my voice
and float.

16:18.701 --> 16:21.867
As you listen to my voice,
keep breathing,

16:21.933 --> 16:24.467
